# Iconography Policy — Agentic Design System

Use this rule when generating or editing UI that includes icons. It ensures a single, consistent icon system across the product.

---

## 1. Allowed icon source

- **Only Material Design icons** are permitted.
- Use [Material Symbols](https://fonts.google.com/icons) (Google Fonts) or the [Material Design Icons](https://materialdesignicons.com/) set.
- Do **not** use Font Awesome, Heroicons, Phosphor, Lucide, or any other icon library. Do not introduce custom or third-party icon sets.

---

## 2. Naming and style

- Refer to icons by their **Material name** (e.g. `add`, `close`, `delete`, `edit`, `settings`, `search`, `arrow_back`, `check_circle`).
- Prefer **outlined** or **rounded** style by default unless the design specifies filled.
- Default size **24dp** for UI; 20dp for compact contexts; 18dp only when necessary.

---

## 3. Implementation

- When generating code, use Material Symbols (e.g. via Google Fonts) or an official Material Icons package. Ensure SVG or icon components come from the Material Design Icons set only.
- If no exact Material icon exists for a concept, choose the closest semantic match from the Material set; do not substitute another library.

---

## 4. Accessibility

- Icon-only buttons must have an **accessible name** (`aria-label`). See accessibility policy for full requirements.
- Decorative icons that duplicate adjacent text must use `aria-hidden="true"`.

---

## 5. Quick reference for the agent

When generating UI:

- **Use only Material Design icons.** No other icon systems.
- Use official Material names and consistent style (outlined/rounded).
- Default size 24dp; 20dp/18dp only when layout requires it.
- Give every interactive icon an accessible name; use `aria-hidden` for redundant decorative icons.

Full policy: `design-system/policies/iconography.md`.
